{
  "_version": "3.0",
  "_exported": "2026-03-04T10:26:38.506Z",
  "projectOrder": null,
  "basementOrder": null,
  "textChanges": [
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(1)",
      "content": "<p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve; font-size: 0.92rem;\">Fara Frog is a week-long project, taking from the arcade genre, trying to make a very simple game be player infinitely. </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Making the procedural generation part of the gameplay, focussing it on the obstacles that procedurally generate with the level. </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Custom score system encourages completing the levels as fast as possible. Starting with the full points that decrease over time wanting to complete the level before points run out.\n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\"></span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The start points for the level are also procedurally generated, scaling with the amount and type of specific obstacles on the map.</span></p>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    },
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(2)",
      "content": "<p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve; font-size: 0.92rem;\">The Design Principle of was the procedurally generated levels, should have quite low restrictions, keeping its simplicity, which also makes some levels unfair. &nbsp;</span></p><span style=\"font-size: 0.92rem; white-space-collapse: preserve; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\">Adding some additional rules to ensure completion, like no shooting tiles within 3 tiles form the spawn (with projectiles having lifetime of 3) to have at least one spawn tile where player can evade all the projectiles.</span>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    },
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(3)",
      "content": "<h4 class=\"bp-heading\" style=\"color: rgb(237, 233, 246); font-size: medium; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve; font-size: 0.92rem;\">Procedural Generation: </span></h4>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    },
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(4)",
      "content": "<p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The level generation for this project is probably one of the simplest I've done, but also effectively entertaining and showcasing quite a lot of diverse challenges.</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The first step is Defining a path using a random walk, weighted to do random range of turns, and setting the first tile at the bottom as spawn tile and last one at the top as the final tile. </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Then filling the remaining space with the pool of 'obstacle tiles':</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Rocket tile that picks one random floor tile and puts a marker there that shoots on trigger enter with a player. \n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Spinning saw that then pick a random distance to spawn a saw and move it around the tile. \n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Saw on the line that if has a pair and cna draw a line form one tile to the pair tile that crosses the path then creates a line with a saw traversing front and back. &nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.92rem; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Key tiles, for each key tile it creates one lock on the final tile that opens on trigger enter with corresponding key. If key tile is not adjacent to the path tile then it despawns. </span></p>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    },
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(5)",
      "content": "<h4 class=\"bp-heading\" style=\"color: rgb(237, 233, 246); font-size: medium; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\">Original&nbsp;<span style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve; font-size: 0.92rem;\">Design document:</span></h4>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    },
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(6)",
      "content": "<p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:3}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Pitch:\n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">\"Frog going up in a narrow place trough various obstacles, l</span><span style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve; font-size: 0.92rem;\">ike moving platforms, projectiles, explosions.\" </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve; font-size: 0.92rem;\"><br></span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">-3x7 or 3x11 map with random path generated, with minimum two direction changed. \n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Random Walls, parts of the walls can be generated other be a rocket launchers which will then randomly target layers on the ground. </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Frog can dash and trough a special tile that go up to the higher platform where falling will not kill you but land you on random path way  </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The higher platforms are thin, and has birds moving and trying to push you down, some projectiles, and rocket launchers. </span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">!Collectible party hats!</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">On the highest possible path ill spawn a single exit tile</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Obstacles:\n</span></p><ul style=\"font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:55,&quot;1&quot;:186,&quot;2&quot;:49,&quot;3&quot;:227,&quot;4&quot;:37,&quot;5&quot;:211,&quot;6&quot;:220,&quot;7&quot;:48,&quot;8&quot;:110,&quot;9&quot;:86,&quot;10&quot;:183,&quot;11&quot;:144,&quot;12&quot;:159,&quot;13&quot;:59,&quot;14&quot;:38,&quot;15&quot;:88},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Every obstacle has a low chance of turning into a collectible if it neighbours a path. \n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:250,&quot;1&quot;:191,&quot;2&quot;:211,&quot;3&quot;:146,&quot;4&quot;:84,&quot;5&quot;:69,&quot;6&quot;:65,&quot;7&quot;:42,&quot;8&quot;:217,&quot;9&quot;:105,&quot;10&quot;:113,&quot;11&quot;:91,&quot;12&quot;:37,&quot;13&quot;:25,&quot;14&quot;:176,&quot;15&quot;:102},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">If door pad is next to a path, it creates a doors at the exit position. There can be numerous, and each has a randomised colour (same colour for the door pad and doors) remember to later readjust the border.  (Door pads later reimagined into a Key runes)\n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:155,&quot;1&quot;:164,&quot;2&quot;:104,&quot;3&quot;:70,&quot;4&quot;:81,&quot;5&quot;:204,&quot;6&quot;:65,&quot;7&quot;:243,&quot;8&quot;:112,&quot;9&quot;:187,&quot;10&quot;:237,&quot;11&quot;:250,&quot;12&quot;:243,&quot;13&quot;:31,&quot;14&quot;:205,&quot;15&quot;:99},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Rocket launchers, no matter where they are, it gets the number of them in the scene if its 5, then mark random 5 path tiles (layer Path) which are next to each other and spawns a rocket and rocket mark when player enters it,  rocket goes up and then each hit the rocket mark, destroy and turn into an explosion.\n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:89,&quot;1&quot;:39,&quot;2&quot;:21,&quot;3&quot;:91,&quot;4&quot;:225,&quot;5&quot;:1,&quot;6&quot;:33,&quot;7&quot;:156,&quot;8&quot;:223,&quot;9&quot;:67,&quot;10&quot;:44,&quot;11&quot;:188,&quot;12&quot;:67,&quot;13&quot;:134,&quot;14&quot;:97,&quot;15&quot;:123},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Blocks with swinging saw, or two saws on the opposite directions\n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:175,&quot;1&quot;:199,&quot;2&quot;:5,&quot;3&quot;:144,&quot;4&quot;:78,&quot;5&quot;:148,&quot;6&quot;:118,&quot;7&quot;:76,&quot;8&quot;:44,&quot;9&quot;:177,&quot;10&quot;:20,&quot;11&quot;:195,&quot;12&quot;:133,&quot;13&quot;:165,&quot;14&quot;:243,&quot;15&quot;:35},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Blocks which propel sow in a straight line, the line is only valid when it crosses path at some point\n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:79,&quot;1&quot;:45,&quot;2&quot;:32,&quot;3&quot;:127,&quot;4&quot;:180,&quot;5&quot;:131,&quot;6&quot;:241,&quot;7&quot;:122,&quot;8&quot;:140,&quot;9&quot;:178,&quot;10&quot;:31,&quot;11&quot;:50,&quot;12&quot;:141,&quot;13&quot;:226,&quot;14&quot;:119,&quot;15&quot;:76},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Turret tower, every time player moves it has a chance to shoot a projectile at player\n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:74,&quot;1&quot;:132,&quot;2&quot;:135,&quot;3&quot;:76,&quot;4&quot;:9,&quot;5&quot;:129,&quot;6&quot;:178,&quot;7&quot;:241,&quot;8&quot;:194,&quot;9&quot;:208,&quot;10&quot;:72,&quot;11&quot;:119,&quot;12&quot;:94,&quot;13&quot;:204,&quot;14&quot;:249,&quot;15&quot;:93},&quot;done&quot;:false}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">[X] Hot wall, if player around it and input system input is clicked and corresponding to his wall position to player position then it will deal dmg \n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:123,&quot;1&quot;:153,&quot;2&quot;:165,&quot;3&quot;:173,&quot;4&quot;:98,&quot;5&quot;:68,&quot;6&quot;:233,&quot;7&quot;:134,&quot;8&quot;:176,&quot;9&quot;:154,&quot;10&quot;:248,&quot;11&quot;:212,&quot;12&quot;:39,&quot;13&quot;:223,&quot;14&quot;:234,&quot;15&quot;:125},&quot;done&quot;:false}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">[X] Spike, if near a path tile then it can spawn a spikes on it, for some time randomly and turn it off for a moment periodically.   after setting everything up, spawn a player prefab at the lowest possible path tile. And make a custom border made of border tiles, around the level\n</span></p></li><li><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4,&quot;style&quot;:103,&quot;writingDirection&quot;:1,&quot;todo&quot;:{&quot;todoUUID&quot;:{&quot;0&quot;:0,&quot;1&quot;:253,&quot;2&quot;:229,&quot;3&quot;:201,&quot;4&quot;:197,&quot;5&quot;:8,&quot;6&quot;:61,&quot;7&quot;:109,&quot;8&quot;:213,&quot;9&quot;:111,&quot;10&quot;:126,&quot;11&quot;:58,&quot;12&quot;:194,&quot;13&quot;:36,&quot;14&quot;:36,&quot;15&quot;:148},&quot;done&quot;:true}}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">The rift, if there is a row that goes trough a path it can be erased and substituted wiht the void tiles and have on it spawned a single path tile which moves left right trough all the void tiles (if player on the platform it moves along with the platform)</span></p></li></ul>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    },
    {
      "selector": "[data-project-id=\"creature-rpg\"] .bproject-content p.bp-text:nth-of-type(7)",
      "content": "<p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Score System:</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Time spent on a level will decrease the multiplier by 0.1 for each second from max x1.5 (apply this multiplies at the end)</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Unlocking each door gives +250\n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">If rift in the level, then later on count +888\n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">For each saw add +100\n</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">For each explosion triggered +50</span></p><p style=\"color: rgba(237, 233, 246, 0.855); font-size: 14.72px; background-color: rgba(14, 8, 32, 0.5);\"><span data-tt=\"{&quot;paragraphStyle&quot;:{&quot;alignment&quot;:4}}\" style=\"white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Each party hat gives you +1000 (this as only thing applied after the multiplier)</span></p>",
      "styles": "",
      "classes": "bp-text",
      "projectId": "creature-rpg"
    }
  ],
